                "description": "This quaint, historic neighborhood was the vision of developer E.P. Janes, who built over 160 homes in a concentrated area of West Altadena during the 1920s housing boom (1924\u20131926). Because of its highly distinct architectural character, it was designated as an official Altadena Heritage Area in 2002. The neighborhood is famous for its collection of storybook 'cute cottages'. These homes heavily feature classic English Cottage/Tudor Revival details, including steeply pitched roofs, half-timbering, prominent brick or stone chimneys, and whimsical, fairytale-like arched entryways.",
