        "description": "Bel Air was founded in 1923 by oil magnate Alphonzo Bell on part of the former Rancho San Jose de Buenos Ayres. Bell subdivided 1,700 acres into expansive residential lots, naming the community \"Bel Air\" \u2014 a name drawn from two sources: the rancho's original meaning of \"good air\" (buenos ayres) and Mrs. Bell's admiration of the Italian word bello, meaning beautiful. Together with Beverly Hills and Holmby Hills, it forms Los Angeles's famed \"Platinum Triangle,\" the trifecta of the city's most exclusive and storied residential enclaves. Accessed primarily via Sunset Boulevard through its landmark gates, Bel Air remains a byword for discreet, old-money luxury amid the canyons of the Santa Monica Mountains."
