                "description": "One of the most recognizable filming locations in Los Angeles, this monumental Art Deco complex is embedded in the visual memory of American popular culture. Its exterior served for decades as the establishing shot in the opening credits of the soap opera General Hospital, making it instantly familiar to generations of television viewers. Its imposing architecture has granted it remarkable versatility on screen \u2014 it has doubled as a high-security prison, a futuristic laboratory, a government complex, and a wartime hospital in productions including Network and Halloween II. Now repurposed as a USC Health Sciences campus, the historic core of the building has been preserved.",
