                "lng": -118.3359266,
                "address": "3400 Warner Blvd, Burbank, CA 91505, USA",
                "description": "First National Pictures built the 62-acre lot in 1926; Warner Bros. acquired control in 1928 after the success of The Jazz Singer. Stage 16 (1937) became one of the world\u2019s largest soundstages, complete with a 2 million-gallon water tank. The lot fostered pre-code gangster classics (Little Caesar, 1931), Looney Tunes, and film noirs (Casablanca, 1942), and later TV hits (Friends, Two and a Half Men). Today, the 110-acre facility\u2014replete with 36 stages and backlot streets\u2014anchors Warner Bros. film & television production worldwide.",
