                "lng": -118.2593318,
                "mapUrl": "https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=34.0852531,-118.2593318",
                "description": "A foundational site in the history of cinema, this Glendale Boulevard address was the original production hub of Mack Sennett's Keystone Studios during the \"Edendale\" era of filmmaking in the 1910s. Here the Keystone Cops were born \u2014 the chaotic, slapstick police characters whose anarchic shorts defined early silent comedy and made Sennett the \"King of Comedy.\" Most significantly, it is where Charlie Chaplin first appeared on screen in 1914, making his celluloid debut and beginning one of the most consequential careers in the history of art. While the original massive stages no longer stand, a historical marker designates the site for those tracing the Edendale film colony that predated Hollywood as the center of the American film industry.",
