                "lng": -118.24696,
                "mapUrl": "https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=34.08824,-118.24696",
                "description": "A pedestrian stairway cutting through one of the steepest residential corridors in the United States \u2014 Baxter Street itself carries a harrowing 32% grade. The stairs offer a safer, scenic alternative for residents and hikers navigating the ridge, rewarding the climb with panoramic views spanning the Downtown LA skyline, the Hollywood Sign, and the San Gabriel Mountains. Part of the legendary network of \"Secret Stairs\" built in the early 20th century to connect hillside residents to the Red Car trolley lines below, the Baxter stairs are a tangible remnant of the pedestrian infrastructure that shaped Echo Park long before the automobile era.",
