                "description": "Perhaps the most culturally significant public stairway in Los Angeles. These 133 steps on Vendome Street served as the primary location for Laurel and Hardy's 1932 Oscar-winning short film The Music Box, in which the duo famously attempts to haul a piano up the brutal incline \u2014 a gag sequence that remains one of the most beloved in comedy history. A commemorative plaque at the base marks the site, which remains largely unchanged since filming. Every year the neighborhood hosts a \"Music Box Day\" festival celebrating both the film and the stairway's enduring legacy as a piece of living cinematic history.",
