                "type": "landmark",
                "description": "The History: Constructed in 1912 before the city established a 15% grade limit, Eldred Street features an incredible 33.3% grade. It is the steepest urban roadway in California and the third steepest in the United States.\n\nThe Character: The ascent is so extreme that mailboxes are located at the bottom of the hill because standard postal trucks cannot navigate the climb, and the city must use specialized miniature garbage trucks to prevent tipping during collection. At the dead-end top, a 196-step wooden staircase leads pedestrians up to Cross Avenue.",
