                "name": "Runyon Canyon Park",
                "description": "A staple of modern Hollywood life whose history stretches back to the silent film era. The canyon was once the estate of George Carman, later owned by Huntington Hartford, and its rugged terrain was used as a backdrop for early westerns and outdoor scenes well before it became a public park. Today Runyon Canyon is the quintessential \"Hollywood hike\" \u2014 the most see-and-be-seen outdoor destination in the city, a place where celebrities, dogs, and film crews coexist on the same dusty trails, and the canyon floor has appeared in reality TV and film countless times as a shorthand for the LA lifestyle.",
