                "description": "Arguably the most photographed house in the world. Designed by Pierre Koenig in 1959 as part of the Arts & Architecture Case Study House Program, Case Study House #22 features a glass-walled living room cantilevered dramatically over the Hollywood Hills with panoramic views of the Los Angeles basin. Julius Shulman's famous 1960 night photograph \u2014 two women in cocktail attire silhouetted against the glittering city below \u2014 became the defining image of mid-century California optimism and has been reproduced millions of times. The house has appeared in dozens of films including Galaxy Quest and Smokin' Aces, and remains privately owned but available for tours.",
