                "name": "The John Cassavetes & Gena Rowlands Estate",
                "description": "Built in 1940 in a Traditional / Hollywood Regency style, this estate was the creative sanctuary for one of cinema's most legendary power couples for over 60 years: pioneering independent filmmaker John Cassavetes and acclaimed actress Gena Rowlands. The home practically served as an active production studio, where masterpieces like A Woman Under the Influence and Faces were written, edited, or staged in part. Obscured by mature trees on nearly an acre, the 4,300-square-foot traditional home is known for its spacious rooms, wood-beamed ceilings, and a converted garage that Cassavetes utilized as his primary film editing suite.",
