                "mapUrl": "https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=34.1085541,-118.3212197",
                "description": "Built in the 1920s as part of the original Hollywoodland development to help hillside residents descend to the village shops and streetcar lines below. The granite stairs wind through deeply shaded residential lanes, offering framed views of the Hollywood Sign as you climb \u2014 the same sign that originally read \"Hollywoodland\" when these steps were new. Part of the larger network of \"Secret Stairs\" that once connected the canyon's hillside homes to the transit grid below, the Beachwood stairs are among the most historically intact and scenically rewarding in the city.",
