                "description": "The History: Originally developed in 1923 as \"Hollywoodland,\" an upscale residential tract. The world-famous Hollywood Sign was originally erected as a massive $21,000 temporary billboard to advertise this specific real estate development.\n\nKey Features: The neighborhood is a living museum of Storybook and Mediterranean Revival architecture. It is famous for its network of historic public staircases, like the Hollywoodland Stairs, built to aid residents in navigating the steep terrain before the prevalence of automobiles. The Beachwood Cafe remains the geographical and social heart of the canyon.",
