                "name": "Hollywood Hills - Laurel Canyon",
                "description": "The Legacy: Known globally as the epicenter of the counterculture folk-rock scene of the 1960s and 70s. It was the creative home for legends like Joni Mitchell, Jim Morrison, Carole King, and Frank Zappa.\n\nNeighborhood Character: Defined by its winding, narrow roads and a rustic \"country-in-the-city\" atmosphere. The neighborhood's history stretches back to the early 1900s when it featured the first commercial \"trackless trolley\" in the U.S. It remains a secluded retreat centered around the historic Canyon Country Store, where the \"Ladies of the Canyon\" used to gather.",
