                "address": "Mount Olympus, Los Angeles, CA 90046, USA",
                "description": "The History: Developed starting in 1963 by actor-turned-developer Russ Vincent. Vincent transformed rugged hillside terrain previously known as \"goatland\" into a high-end community designed as a \"monument to luxury.\"\n\nThe Theme: Every street is named after figures or places from Greek mythology, such as Zeus Drive, Apollo Drive, Hercules Drive, and Achilles Drive.\n\nArchitectural Style: Known for its wide, paved streets and underground utilities (a rarity for the hills). The neighborhood is defined by large-scale, dramatic Mediterranean and contemporary mansions with Greco-Roman statuary and columns, all positioned to maximize panoramic views of the LA basin and the Pacific Ocean.",
