                "description": "Completed in 1924 for rare-book dealer Alice Millard, La Miniatura is the first and most celebrated of Frank Lloyd Wright's four Los Angeles-area concrete textile-block houses \u2014 the others being the Storer House, the Freeman House, and the Ennis House. Nestled in a eucalyptus-shaded ravine in Pasadena, the house takes its nickname from its relatively modest scale, which belies the intricate geometric patterning of its hand-cast concrete blocks and the dramatic way it engages the landscape. Wright considered it one of his finest achievements, writing that it proved a beautiful house could be built for modest means. It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places and remains privately owned.",
