        "description": "An engineering marvel completed in 1915, this was the first paved highway to bridge the gap between Los Angeles and the Central Valley. Now largely bypassed by Interstate 5, the surviving segments of the \"Castaic-Tejon Route\" serve as a preserved time capsule of early motoring history, featuring crumbling foundations of long-lost roadside inns and original concrete slabs."
