                "lat": 34.022186,
                "lng": -118.27901,
                "description": "Towering over the 110 freeway near downtown Los Angeles, the massive three-sided neon sign featuring Felix the Cat has been a beloved beacon for commuters since 1958. Felix the Cat was licensed to the dealership's original owner, Winslow Felix, who was friends with the character's creator, Pat Sullivan. The sign is deeply ingrained in LA's car culture and is one of the largest and most famous neon automotive signs on the West Coast. The dealership itself has been operating since the 1920s, making it one of the oldest in the city.",
