        "description": "Athens-Westmont and West Athens-Westmont are terms often used interchangeably by government agencies to describe this large unincorporated area of Los Angeles County. Unlike surrounding communities, it falls outside the City of Los Angeles city limits and is policed by the L.A. County Sheriff's Department rather than the LAPD. Bounded roughly by the City of Los Angeles to the north and east, Inglewood and Hawthorne to the west, and Gardena to the south, the area is anchored by Los Angeles Southwest College and the Metro C Line (Green) Vermont/Athens Station."
