                "description": "Designed by Jack A. Charney\u2014a prot\u00e9g\u00e9 of legendary modernist architects Richard Neutra and Rudolph Schindler\u2014and completed in 1965, this 31-story building is a towering landmark of mid-century design. Situated at the base of the Hollywood Hills, it holds the distinction of being the tallest residential tower in the greater Los Angeles area, offering unparalleled prestige and privacy. Characterized by sleek, minimalist architecture with floor-to-ceiling glass doors and expansive private terraces. Provides sweeping, unobstructed jetliner views that stretch from the downtown skyline all the way to the Pacific Ocean. Maintains a long-standing reputation as an ultra-glamorous haven for the entertainment industry's elite, with past and present residents including Cher, Elton John, and Sidney Poitier.",
