                "description": "The Context: Designated as a Historic Preservation Overlay Zone (HPOZ) in 2008, Wilshire Park is a remarkably intact residential enclave.\n\nNeighborhood Character: The area is celebrated for its diverse and well-preserved collection of early 20th-century architecture, including Craftsman, Dutch Colonial, Spanish Colonial Revival, and Prairie Style homes. It offers a quieter, residential look at the expansion of Los Angeles during the \"Wilshire boom\" of the 1920s.",
